  <h3 align="justify">Uploading and unzipping</h3>
                                <p align="justify">To start working with Magento you need to upload files to your hosting server. This can be done using your hosting file manager or or using an alternative FTP client.</p>
                                <div align="justify">
                                    Select the <strong>"unzip.php"</strong> and the <strong>"fullpackage.zip"</strong> files and upload them to your server. Type the path to the <strong>"unzip.php"</strong> file on your server (http://your_domain_name/unzip.php) in your
                                    <abbr title="Internet Explorer, Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Opera, Safari etc.">browser</abbr>. You will see the following screen:
                                </div>
                                <figure class="img-polaroid">
                                    <div align=""><img src="img/magento/complete-install-unzip-php.jpg" alt="Unzip.php initial screen."></div>
                                </figure>
                                <div align="justify">In the <strong>"Choose your zip file"</strong> select box please choose the uploaded <strong>fullpackage.zip</strong> file.</div>
                                <div align="justify">In the <strong>"Unzip to"</strong> field specify the folder to unzip the files.</div>
                                <div align="justify">Click the <strong>"Unzip"</strong> button.</div>
                                <p align="justify" class="alert alert-warning"><span>Make sure you've set the correct permissions type for the unzipping files folder. The permissions should be <strong>CHMOD 755 or 777</strong>, depending on your server configuration. </span></p>